trans-unit.source: Provides properties and methods for composing a `RouteValue` expression at design time.
A visual designer host, such as [!INCLUDE[vsprvslong](~/includes/vsprvslong-md.md)], uses the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.RouteValueExpressionEditor> class to compose a `RouteValue` markup expression.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.Design.RouteValueExpressionEditor"></xref> class.
Evaluates a `RouteValue` expression and provides the design-time value.

The visual designer uses the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.RouteValueExpressionEditor.EvaluateExpression%2A> method to evaluate a `RouteValue` expression and to provide the design-time value for an associated control property.
The expression does not include the `RouteValue` expression prefix.
An object that contains additional parsing information that is used to evaluate the expression.
The type of the control property.
A service provider implementation that is supplied by the designer host and that is used to obtain additional design-time services.
The value of the specified URL parameter if the expression evaluation succeeded; otherwise, `null`.
Returns an expression editor sheet for a `RouteValue` expression.
The <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.RouteValueExpressionEditor.GetExpressionEditorSheet%2A> method returns an editor-sheet implementation for `RouteValue` expressions.
The editor sheet for `RouteValue` expressions enables users to select a URL parameter.
After users have selected the parameter, the editor-sheet implementation generates a `RouteValue` expression that is returned to the visual designer.
The expression string that is used to initialize the expression editor sheet.
The expression does not include the `RouteValue` expression prefix.
A service provider implementation that is supplied by the designer host and that is used to obtain additional design-time services.
A <xref href="System.Web.UI.Design.RouteValueExpressionEditorSheet"></xref> instance that defines the `RouteValue` expression properties.
